        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2"> Here's my solution:</P><P>AAXP Skill Spell: Kiss of Death<BR>Classes: Necromancer level 59 <BR> <BR>Description: <BR> <BR>DoT for 24366 Hit Points (HP) in 56 ticks</P><P>Details: <BR>Mana: 250<BR>Casting Time: 24.00 seconds<BR>Recast Time: 72.00 minutes<BR>Skill: Alteration<BR>Allowed Targets: All<BR>Resist: None<BR>Range to target: 400<BR> <BR>Messages: <BR>Cast on you: You have been kissed by Death.<BR>Cast on other: A Moss Snake has been kissed by Death.<BR>Cast by you: :gives a Moss Snake the kiss of Death.</P><P>Reageant: <BR>Essence Emerald (1)</P><P>Level Restrictions:<BR>Must be cast on MoB above level 55.<BR>--------------------------------------------------------------</P><P>This DoT would last 5.6 minutes, but doing an incredible 24,366 damage to whatever MoB you are fighting. The reageant would be an Essence Emerald (finally - a viable use!) This spell could also not be cast upon anything lower than level 55 (thus disallowing any use on 32k HP Kunark MoBs) as that would INSANELY overpower Necromancers. Even though this spell seems to do an unworldly amount of damage, (even being UNresistable) this is still only a small impact against the SoL MoBs who have over 100,000 HP. Also, this spell would be un-castable against a PC - as that would make Necromancer's the master of PVP (1 DoT kills you - no matter what)</P><P>THIS is the solution to Necromantic problems on raids - with this kind of damage, those stupid melees will be forced to Sacrifice themselves to give the Necromancer the EE component to cast the spell.<BR>*A possible way to do this is to have the necro Sacrifice a player right before he dies - he would die anyway, he gets rezzed back to corpse, though not for exp, and helps the raid do 24.3k damage to the MoB by dying.</P><P>Imagine this - Necro's more wanted on raids than Wizzies with their panzy 20k dmg ManaBurns. Also, since this is a CLASS AAXP skill, it will not even be available to anyone under 59 - but being an AAXP skill, there wont be any whining about the rareness of the spell :)</P><P><BR>~just my 2cp - hope this all made sense</P><P><img src="http://www.imahosting.com/sigs/azumaan1.jpg" border=0><br><font size=1><b><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=54401" target="_blank">Azumaan</a></b><br>30 Erudite Necromancer<br>Silver Faith<br>Mithaniel Marr</font id=size1></P><P>Edited by - Azumaan Necromaan on 04/08/2002  14:57:35</P><P>Edited by - Azumaan Necromaan on 04/08/2002  15:03:49</P><P>Edited by - Azumaan Necromaan on 04/08/2002  15:25:37<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
